    "client_msg_id": "66FD59CE-0A8A-4192-8D99-94B7977EAB8C",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Jokes aside — JS has long had a culture of _choose your own syntax_ (and, to a limited extent, semantics) with things like Coffee, JSX, ClojureScript, and now TypeScript. So I think it's fair to say JavaScript is _not just_ JavaScript — there's the browser and node runtimes, there's the transpiled languages, there's the npm ecosystem, there's the framework-centric culture, and more, all of them different, all of them opt-in, all of them desirable and offensive.",
    "user": "UC2A2ARPT",
    "ts": "1707279299.951199",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "a9z4v",
